    "Harvey Cox, Henry M. Morris": "\u201311\nThe Litter of Solomon `[char_Solomon_Ref]`\nJust as the Song urges us to turn our gaze toward the beloved stand\u00ad\ning outside the wall of the woman\u2019s house in 2:9 (\u201cLook, there\nhe stands .\u00a0.\u00a0.\u201d), it focuses our imagination on the procession as it\n[v_Sng_3_7] approaches: \u201cLook, it is the litter of Solomon `[char_Solomon_Ref]`!\u201d (3:7). Song 3:7\u201311\nis framed by the invitation to look deeply, offered first to us and then\nto the daughters of Jerusalem, who once more make a place for us in\nthe poem.\nWhat do we see when we look? First, we see sixty armed men, \u201cthe\nmighty men of Israel,\u201d whose swords protect against \u201calarms by night.\u201d\nLike the sentinels who appear in 3:3, these soldiers\u2014\u201cequipped\n87. \u0007Rabbi Ezra ben Solomon `[char_Solomon_Ref]` of Gerona,Commentary on the Song of Songs,",
    "John Trapp": "And I said after she had done.] Or, Yet I said; but I lost my sweet words upon her.\nVer.\n7. He hath hedged me about. ] Sorrounded me with troubles, brought me into straits inextricable and importable.\nVer.\n7. He hath hedged me about.] Sorrounded me with troubles, brought me into straits inextricable and importable.\nVer.\n7. Ver.\n7. Her Nazarites.] Who served God in a singular way of abstinence above other men. These had their rules given them, {#Nu 6:1-21} which while they observed, They were purer than snow, whiter than milk.] Temperance is the mother of beauty, as luxury is of deformity. This is nothing to the Popish votaries, those epicures and abbey lubbers: \u201c Quorum luxuriae totus non sufficit orbis.\u201d Some by Nazarites here understand their nobles, and such as wore coronets on their heads. Nezar is a crown; {#2Sa 1:10 2Ki 11:12} thus [v_Gen_49_26] Joseph `[char_Joseph_Ref]` was a Nazarite; {#Ge 49:26} so Daniel and his three associates, in whom that was verified, \u201c Gratior est pulchro veniens in corpore virtus.\u201d\nVer.\n7. But the house of Israel will not hearken unto thee. ] They will not. See the like, #Joh 5:40 8:44 . A man\u2019s will is his hell, saith Bernard. And it is easier, saith another, to deal with twenty men\u2019s reasons, than with one man\u2019s will. What hope is there of those that will not hear; or, if they do, yet have made their conclusion beforehand, and will stir no more than a stake in the midst of a stream? For they will not hearken unto me. ] Speaking unto them in the Scriptures. See #Ho 8:12 Mt 10:24,25 Joh 15:18 , &amp;c. Let this speech of God to the prophet comfort faithful ministers, contra cervicosos et cerebrosos istos hypocritas, that reject or resist their preaching. What are we that we may not be slighted, whenas Christ himself the arch-prophet is? Impudent. ] Heb., Stiff of forehead. This was a point next the worst. Illum ego periisse dice cui periit pudor, said that heathen: { a } he is an undone man who is past shame. { a } Curtius.\nVer.\n7. But the house of Israel will not hearken unto thee.] They [v_Jhn_5_40] will not. See the like, #Joh 5:40 8:\n7. God fathers that rebellious people upon Moses `[char_Moses_Exo_2]`. Whether they will hear, or whether they will forbear,] q.d., Let them choose; and if they have a mind to it, be miserable by their [v_Ezk_2_5] own election. See #Eze 2:\n7. All the people, nations, and languages fell down. ] They that come of the yielding willow, and not of the sturdy oak, will yield with the time, and ever be of the king\u2019s religion. In Queen Mary `[char_Mary_Ref]`\u2019s days here, and so in the Palatinate lately, scarce one in five hundred stood out, but fell to Popery as fast as leaves fall in autumn. See on #Da 3:5 .\nVer.\n7. All the people, nations, and languages fell down.] They that come of the yielding willow, and not of the sturdy oak, will yield with the time, and ever be of the king\u2019s religion. In Queen Mary `[char_Mary_Ref]`\u2019s days here, and so in the Palatinate lately, scarce one in five hundred stood out, but fell to Popery as fast as leaves fall in [v_Dan_3_5] autumn. See on #Da 3:"
